                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <p>The main text was copied in a <term type="script">mixed
                                        minuscule</term> script, with variable slant, in brown ink,
                                    with moderate variation in letter size.</p>
                                <p>Syllabic abbreviations and superscript word endings appear only
                                    at the end of lines. Breathings are round and mute <hi rend="italic">iota</hi> is absent or subscript. There is
                                    decorative use of the double dot, and accentuation of all
                                        <foreign xml:lang="la">nomina sacra</foreign>.</p>
                                <p>Punctuation used includes the middle and upper points and full
                                    stop.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>

                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="colInit">The beginnings of hymns are marked by minor
                                initials in red ink.</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
